# Trigger lexicon — which words fire which capability

A **reference index, not a policy.** It tells you (and the agent) the phrasings that
reliably invoke each skill, when *not* to invoke it, and which capabilities are
**commands** you must call explicitly. Skills auto-fire from their `description`;
commands do not — you type them.

## The reliability rule

> If a capability cannot be triggered **reliably** from written context — because its
> trigger words collide with another skill, or because it fans out subagents (a
> non-obvious, expensive action a description rarely fires on its own) — it is a
> **command**, invoked explicitly, not a description-triggered skill.

The fan-outs (`coverage`, `cross-examine`) and the comprehension gate (`comprehend`) are
commands for exactly this reason: you decide when the cost is worth it; the model does
not guess.

## Generic capabilities (the `psotobverse-utils` plugin — always available)

| Capability | Kind | Reliable triggers | When NOT |
|---|---|---|---|
| `deliberate` | skill | "design this", "how should I approach", "architecture", "refactor deeply", "this is delicate", "tackle this weird bug" | trivial / mechanical one-liners |
| `goal` | skill | "work toward / track this objective", multi-step execution with a backlog | a single self-contained step |
| `index` | skill | "organize / index the repo", "split this oversize doc", "find loose files" | a content-coherence question (use `reconcile`) |
| `reconcile` | skill | "audit coherence", "docs-vs-code drift", "find contradictions / redundancies" | a file-placement mess (use `tidy`/`index`) |
| `tidy` | skill | "relocate / move misplaced files", "where should this live" | rewriting content (not a move) |
| `reflect` | command | at a checkpoint / session end; "capture the lesson", "close the learning loop" | mid-task with nothing learned yet |
| `audit-report` | command | "structure this multi-agent audit output" | a small finding that fits inline |
| `sync-cowork` | command | "refresh the Cowork instructions" | — |
| **`comprehend`** | **command** | "explain what you understood first", "restate the request", "take an exam before planning" | a trivial, unambiguous ask |
| **`coverage`** | **command** | "make sure you didn't miss a relevant policy", "what policies apply here", "sweep for anything off-path" | when `comprehend` already ran it this session |
| **`cross-examine`** | **command** | "review this thoroughly", "adversarial / red-team check", "fan out reviewers", "cross-examine the findings" | a quick single-pass look |

### Automatic (hooks — no trigger words; they fire on events)

| Hook | Fires on | Effect (always **additive**, never blocks reading) |
|---|---|---|
| `policy_router` | prompt / file write matching a `routing.yml` signal | surfaces the next relevant policy (remind), or asks before a load-bearing *write* |
| `comprehension_gate` | first write to a configured path | asks for the comprehension artifact (restate + diagram) first |
| `coverage_sentinel` | a substantive task with no coverage run yet | nudges you to run `/coverage` or `/comprehend` |
